{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "vex", "context": "all", "tags": "search, point", "group": "attrib", "showtags": "true"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["idtopoint"], "extent": [0, 14]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Finds a point by its id attribute."], "extent": [77, 119]}, {"type": "usage_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "usage", "indent": 0, "text": [" ", {"type": "code", "text": ["int idtopoint(<geometry>, int id)"]}], "role": "item", "extent": [119, 164]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Returns the number of the point with the given value in the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["id"]}, " attribute. Returns ", {"type": "code", "text": ["-1"]}, " if no point has the given ID."], "extent": [164, 284]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the geometry doesn\u2019t have an ", {"type": "code", "text": ["id"]}, " attribute, point numbers are used as ids.  In this case, the function will return the given ", {"type": "code", "text": ["id"]}, " value, unless it is greater than the number of points in the source geometry, in which case the function will return ", {"type": "code", "text": ["-1"]}, "."], "extent": [284, 542]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["To look up a point by its ", {"type": "code", "text": ["name"]}, " attribute value, use ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/nametopoint", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "nametopoint()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/nametopoint"}, ". To look up a point by an arbitrary string or int attribute value, use ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/findattribval", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "findattribval()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/findattribval"}, "."], "extent": [542, 707]}, {"type": "arg_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "arg", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["<geometry>"]}], "role": "item", "extent": [16, 35], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When running in the context of a node (such as a wrangle SOP), this argument can be an integer representing the input number (starting at 0) to read the geometry from."], "extent": [58, 235]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Alternatively, the argument can be a string specifying a geometry file (for example, a ", {"type": "code", "text": [".bgeo"]}, ") to read from. When running inside Houdini, this can be an ", {"type": "code", "text": ["op:/path/to/sop"]}, " reference."], "extent": [235, 423]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "geometry"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [736, 745], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/nametopoint", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "nametopoint()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/nametopoint"}], "extent": [745, 766]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/idtoprim", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "idtoprim()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/idtoprim"}], "extent": [766, 783]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/findattribval", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "findattribval()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/findattribval"}], "extent": [783, 806]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["idtopoint"], "summary": ["Finds a point by its id attribute."], "included": ["/vex/functions/_common"]}